djabberd (0.85-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  [Ioan Rogers]
  * Updated to latest version of packaging standards
  * Install systemd service
  * Build-depends on netbase, otherwise ipv6 tests fail in chroot build
  * Build-depend on libauthen-sasl-perl to enable more tests
  * Make lintian happier
  * No writing in /tmp by djabberd.postinst
  * /var/run has become /run and a /tmpfs, so create /run/djabberd in the init
    script instead of the package
  * Removed dependency on libdigest-sha-perl; it is in perl
  * init script lets djabberd handle its own daemonising and PID file
  * init script uses lsb functions for status messages
  * debian-perl group is package maintainer

  [Dominik Schulz (tex) <lkml@ds.gauner.org>]
  * Split djabberd into djabberd and libdjabberd-perl 

 -- Ioan Rogers <ioan@dirtysoft.ca>  Tue, 16 Oct 2012 18:46:12 -0700

